The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems and their phase transitions, which are topics commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The use of survey propagation and population dynamics also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
